data.title: Five Things You Need to Know About Gerald Green
data.meta_description: Who are this year's Phoenix Suns? With the 2014-15 season coming up fast, we look beyond the box scores to find out a little more about this year's squad, both on and off the court. 1. Bolstered by a believer Gerald Green's professional basketball path includes seven NBA teams, the D-league and overseas. In a way, he's back where he started. Suns General Manager Ryan McDonough, then with the Boston Celtics, originally scouted Green in high school. It was McDonough's input that led to Boston drafting him and, more recently, Phoenix trading for him in 2013.
